Hagerman vs. Gateway...OCTOBER 21, 2014. We will be having a Dig Pink Game. Please wear Pink and Come out and support your Lady Cats and a great cause. Junior Varsity game at 4:30, with Varsity following. There will be plenty of great items for auction, along with a bake sale All proceeds will go to the Side Out Foundation to benefit breast cancer research and treatment.

If you are interested in DONATING AUCTION ITEMS, please contact Jennifer Jensen Hamill.

post_text: Congratulations to Hagerman Ladycat, Lori Gossett, for earning a $2500 scholarship from NMAA. NMMA gave 19 scholarships to athletes around the state, and Lori received the Extraordinary Participation Scholarship, which is one of the highest scholarship amounts NMAA has to offer. Lori will be acknowledged at the state basketball tournament in March for he hard work & success in her athletic career. Congratulations, Lori!
